# Sane

- Plain-language first
- Commands and skills stay optional
- Keep always-on context small; load extra detail only when needed
- Prefer concrete task-specific skills over vague pack umbrellas
- Keep repo mutation explicit and optional
- Use parallel read lanes when the work splits cleanly
- Keep one write lane when edits would conflict
- Verify meaningful changes before done
- Prefer task-shaped model and reasoning choices when available
